abstract: European Space Agency astronaut Timothy Peake apologizes on Twitter for dialing wrong number when trying to call home from aboard International Space Station; Peake is first publicly funded British astronaut and recent arrival to space station.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Peake, aboard the International Space Station, took his flub to Twitter, apologizing to “the lady I just called by mistake saying ‘Hello, is this planet Earth?’”

headline.main: Timothy Peake, British Astronaut, Dials Wrong Number From Space
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Science and Health; Calling Earth in 2015: A Space Oddity
